Will definitely be going back if Im in town and in the area looking for a quick good bite and coffee (and tea for my dad).

review_text: After eating from Tim Horton I realise the franchise is taking against indians on behalf of Justin Trudeau government. I have decided to cancel my visa application to Canada after eating from here. The taste was so bad that I now love my Marwari mom kadi chawal. Menu had everything but taste was nothing, the melt cheese & chicken, chicken tikka croissant and for Gods sake Cream bagel should be sent on trial for being so bad. Finally only good thing about this place is customer service & coffee. As we entered the order receiver at the desk said please pay the bill and go even before she punching in, as she realised that we had taken zomato gold offer of 30 percent off. Now after eating I have realised why people dont pay and go post eating here. Starbucks, Theobroma & Even local Bandra bakery make better food than this joint. Merry Christmas became Marry Christmas after eating due to delusion of food that I have just consumed.

review_text: The French Vanilla Latte with Espresso at Tim Hortons is a delightful blend that beautifully marries the rich essence of espresso with the creamy sweetness of French vanilla. The espressos boldness is elegantly balanced by the smoothness of the frothy milk and the inviting sweetness of the vanilla flavor. The drink carries a comforting aroma and a satisfying taste that is not overly sweet, making it a perfect treat for those who enjoy a harmonious balance between coffee and a hint of sweetness. The addition of French vanilla adds a luscious dimension, creating a drink thats both soothing and invigorating. Its a wonderful choice for anyone seeking a mellow yet flavorsome coffee experience.

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of dining at Tim Hortons, and I must say it was quite an enjoyable experience overall. Heres a detailed breakdown of my visit: ** Food: 4/5 ** The food at Tim Hortons is a real treat for the taste buds. I started with their Frozen French Vanilla, and it did not disappoint. It had a smooth and rich vanilla flavor with just the right hint of coffee notes. Served over ice, it was a refreshing way to kick off my meal. For the main course, I tried two different sandwiches. First up was the Chicken & Cheese Melt Sandwich. The sourdough bread was the perfect canvas for the chunky spread of chicken, Cheddar, and grated cheese. It was grilled to perfection with a touch of garlic confit, and the combination of flavors was delightful. Next, I ventured into spicier territory with the Spicy Chicken Melt Sandwich. Again, the sourdough bread was spot on, but the addition of BBQ chicken, green chili, and sriracha sauce gave it a nice kick. While it was enjoyable, I found it slightly less impressive than the Chicken & Cheese Melt. To satisfy my sweet tooth, I ordered a Timbit Box of 10. This assortment of mini donut balls, known as Timbits, was a delightful mix of flavors. The blueberry-filled and chocolate-filled Timbits were my personal favorites, and the caramel crumble and cookies & cream varieties were equally scrumptious. I couldnt leave without trying one of Tim Hortons classic donuts, so I opted for the Boston Cream. This classic was filled with a luscious Boston Cream and dipped in a generous amount of chocolate sauce. While it was tasty, it didnt quite reach the same level of excellence as the sandwiches and Frozen French Vanilla. ** Service: 4/5 ** The service at Tim Hortons was efficient and friendly. The staff took my order promptly, and my food and beverages were prepared quickly. The employees were attentive and made sure I had everything I needed throughout my meal. ** Atmosphere: 3.5/5 ** Tim Hortons is more of a casual, grab-and-go kind of place rather than a sit-down restaurant. The atmosphere is clean and functional, with a focus on fast service. While it may not be the ideal spot for a romantic dinner, its a great place to grab a quick bite to eat or enjoy some coffee and donuts with friends. In conclusion, my visit to Tim Hortons was a satisfying experience. The food, particularly the sandwiches and Frozen French Vanilla, stood out as highlights. The service was efficient, and while the atmosphere was more on the casual side, it served its purpose well. If youre in the mood for tasty sandwiches and delightful coffee beverages, Tim Hortons is a solid choice.

review_text: The bagel came cut in half horizontally which made it really easy to apply the cream cheese using a knife. For the first half of the bagel, I made the mistake of applying the cheese little by little before each bite. By the time the first half was finished it occurred to me that that was a very inefficient way of eating it. So, for the second half I applied the entirety of the remaining cream cheese thickly onto the open half of the half-bagel and only then began eating, which made eating it so much easier and made the experience much more enjoyable. The thickness of the cream cheese also was perfect. It looked very hard but when you spread it on the bagel it spreads very smoothly; the firmness of the bagel also helps when spreading them cream cheese cheeks as it (the bagel) retains its shape even if you press hard on it during the process. The visual factor of seeing the knife s zigzag sharp edge creating crisp lines on the cream is also an additional element which adds to the satisfaction of the whole experience. Seeing the lines created by the sharp edge of the knife on the cheese reminded me of those zen sand gardens which have those beautiful and calming patterns on the sand. If you are having bagel and cream cheese for the first time then make sure you eat it the right way from the start. Also, make sure you sit in a place that has high tables. They have lot of low tables which looks good aesthetically but makes it really hard to eat/drink from it. I wish they would make all the chairs and tables as ergonomically efficient as possible instead of focusing on the instagrammability of it.

review_text: The business was founded by Tim Horton, who played in the National Hockey League, from 1949 until his death in an auto crash in 1974.[14][15] The first Tim Horton restaurant was located in North Bay, Ontario and sold hamburgers.[16] The chains first donut store opened on May 17, 1964 in Hamilton, Ontario under the name Tim Horton Donuts.[17] The name was later abbreviated to Tim Hortons and then changed to Tim Hortons without the possessive apostrophe. Soon after Horton opened the store, he met Ron Joyce, a former police constable in Hamilton. In 1965, Joyce took over the fledgling Tim Horton Donut Shop at 65 Ottawa St N. By 1967, after opening two additional stores, Joyce and Horton became full partners. Upon Hortons death in 1974, Joyce bought out the Horton familys shares for $1 million and took over as sole owner of the existing chain of 40 stores, quickly and aggressively expanding the chain in both geography and product selection. The 500th store opened in 1991.[18] Ron Joyces aggressive expansion of the Tim Hortons business resulted in major changes to the Canadian coffee and donut restaurant market. Many independent donut shops and small chains were driven out of business, while Canadas per-capita ratio of donut shops surpassed that of all other countries.[19] The Horton and Joyce partnership carried on, with the marriage of Joyces son, Ron Joyce Jr., and Hortons eldest daughter, Jeri-Lynn Horton-Joyce, who were joint owners of Tim Hortons franchises in Cobourg, Ontario until 2023 when the couple retired after 37 years.[20] 1990 2002: Name change and growth Edit Tim Hortons logo as used in the mid-1990s The company had originally been incorporated as Tim Donut Limited.[11] By the 1990s, the company name had changed to The TDL Group Ltd. This was an effort by the company to diversify the business, removing the primary emphasis on donuts, and continuing the expansion of the menu options as consumer tastes broadened.[18] Some older locations retain signage with the companys name, including a possessive apostrophe, despite the fact that the official styling of the companys name has been Tim Hortons without an apostrophe for at least a decade.[21] The company had removed the apostrophe after signs using the apostrophe was interpreted by some to be breaking the language sign laws of the Province of Quebec in 1993.[22] The removal of the apostrophe allowed the company to have one common sign image across Canada.[23] Although a number of Quebec locations have bilingual menu boards, the decision to have both Canadian official languages represented is left to the discretion of individual franchise owners. Some Quebec locations have French-only menu boards. It is the strong recommendation to all the Quebec restaurants from the TDL Group Corporation that they post menu boards in both English and French in accordance with the standards being enforced by the Office quebecois de la langue francaise.[24] Merger with Wendys Edit A Tim Hortons/Wendys joint restaurant in Markham, Ontario In 1992, the owner of all Tim Hortons and Wendys Restaurants in Prince Edward Island, Daniel P. Murphy, decided to open new franchise outlets for both brands in the same building in the town of Montague. Murphy invited Joyce and Wendys chairman Dave Thomas to the grand opening of the combo store, where the two executives met for the first time. Murphys success with combining coffee and donuts with Wendys fast food led to the August 8, 1995, acquisition of and merger with TDL Group by Wendys International, Inc., an American company, which lasted until 2009.[25] The sale was widely commented on in the media. In 1995, the Toronto Star had a column reflecting on Tim Hortons selling out to Wendys with the spectacle of another great Canadian icon...gone to Yankee burgerfat.[26] 2002 2006: Regaining independence Edit Tim Hortons franchises spread rapidly and eventually overtook McDonalds as Canadas largest food service

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of visiting Tim Hortons, the renowned Canadian coffee and fast-food chain, right here in Mumbai. Nestled amidst the bustling streets of the city, this franchise brings a taste of Canadian flavors and comforting ambiance to the local scene. From the moment I stepped inside, I was greeted by the familiar aroma of freshly brewed coffee and the warm ambiance that Tim Hortons is known for. The menu boasted a variety of options. I opted for a  cappuccino ,  tim chocolate shake , and  rich truffle slice . The coffee was smooth and well-balanced, a perfect companion for a quick catch-up with a friend or a peaceful moment alone. While the menu included a decent selection of both beverages and food items, I found myself missing some of the seasonal specialties that Tim Hortons is famous for, such as their Tim Hortons Roll Up the Rim contest and various holiday-themed treats. It would be wonderful to see these additions in the future. The seating area was comfortable, ideal for casual meetings or a leisurely afternoon spent reading a book. The bright and cheerful interior, adorned with hints of Canadian culture, added to the overall experience. However, I did notice that during peak hours, the place could get a bit crowded, leading to longer wait times for both ordering and receiving food. It would be great if they could streamline their service during busy periods. All in all, Tim Hortons in Mumbai offers a pleasant escape into Canadian flavors and culture. The cozy ambiance, friendly staff, and a taste of their signature offerings make it a delightful spot to enjoy a cup of coffee and a snack. While there is room for improvement in terms of service efficiency during peak times, I left with a contented palate and a sense of having experienced a slice of Canada in the heart of Mumbai.

review_text: I visited this place for breakfast. They do serve Jain food with very limited options. We had the following vegetarian food 1) Roasted Veggies Croissant Sandwich. 2) Bagel with Cream Cheese, tomato 3) Cappuccino (medium size). They have options for freshly brewed coffee beans- strong roasted or medium roasted beans to make the coffee as per your taste strong or mild. for us Medium was also quite strong but it was too good. Took Chocolate Croissant as a take away. The packing was done quite well. overall: Ill definitely visit this place again. Will definitely come here with my cyclist group after an early morning ride and have lovely coffee and hearty breakfast. Food: 5/5 ( with vegetarian options Im happy) Service: 5/5 (people at the counter were very welcoming) Ambience: 5/5 (the place was well lit up and the music was good) cleanliness: 5/5. No Valet Parking. But can park in the lanes. Free wifi is available. Power plug points given on almost all the tables.

review_text: The all famous canadian coffee brand finally lands in Bombay and it sure has landed with a bang. I tried their all famous frozen french vanilla which had sutble coffee notes with vanilla and it is one of the best cold coffees Ive ever had. I also tried their Iced Americano which was light and rich in flavour. Coming to food, their Timbits were my absolute favourites. Each and every flavor be it cookie and cream or caramel or chocolate or blueberry, I can have em all any day, any time. Tried their cheese melt sandwich too which stands true to its name however if you are not a fan of crusts, reuqest em to decrust it for you. The bagel with cream cheese tomato was refreshing and tasty. All and all, my experience at Tim Hortons was a memorable one. Do try it out for coffee and desserts alike.

review_text: Just loved this new outlet of Tim Hortons!!!

In conclusion, I highly recommend To anyone looking for a fantastic dining experience. The combination of delectable food, cozy ambiance, and attentive service make it a standout choice for a memorable meal. I will definitely be returning to indulge in their culinary delights again soon.

I ve been looking forward to trying out Tim Hortons since a while now and it did not disappoint. The vibes and ambience are top notch and I enjoyed their drinks and food. Would love to chill here more. Food

I was recently looking for a place to grab a quick bite and a cup of coffee, and I decided to try Tim Hortons. I had heard good things about the chain, and I was excited to try it for myself. I was not disappointed! The coffee was delicious, and the Timbits were even better. I also tried the bagel with cream cheese, and it was perfectly toasted. The service was friendly and efficient, and the atmosphere was comfortable. I was really impressed with how Tim Hortons has managed to capture the essence of Canada in its Mumbai location. The decor is reminiscent of a Canadian coffee shop, and the menu features some of Canadas most popular dishes. If youre looking for a taste of Canada in the heart of Mumbai, I highly recommend Tim Hortons. You wont be disappointed! Pros: * Delicious coffee * Fresh Timbits * Comfortable atmosphere * Friendly service * Canadian-inspired menu Cons: * Some items on the menu are not available in India * Can be crowded during peak hours **Overall:** Tim Hortons is a great place to go for a quick bite and a cup of coffee. The food is delicious, the service is friendly, and the atmosphere is comfortable. I highly recommend it!

review_text: Tim Horton- Famous Canadian coffeehouse now in Mumbai that specializes in French coffee, timbits, and unique doughnuts. A wonderful establishment setting ideal for friends gathering and laidback energy. The location is typically pretty busy with shoppers. The vibe of this place is amazing and well lit. Canadian leaf logos are ubiquitous. Their captivating decor and aroma creates a warm and inviting atmosphere. Analysis French vanilla coffee- Frothy French roasted coffee beans and vanilla flavour coming together to form Tim Horton s special coffee. Something different with savory options. Chocolate and Caramel timbits -.Their signature small sized sweet balls in Chocolate and Caramel flavours. Must have here. Caramel donut- Perfect dessert coated with caramel glaze and gooey caramel centre that oozes with every bite. Heavenly irresistible. Mushroom and cheese melt sandwich- Delicious cheezy grilled sandwich with buttery mushroom and cheddar cheese with hint of garlic. Paired with potato chips. Good savory option with sweet offerings. Definitely innovative upscale coffee spot.

review_text: Tim Hortons offers an enticing array of coffee and food options that are sure to please any palate. From rich brews to flavorful snacks, theres something for everyone to enjoy. While the staff is generally good, the self-service setup may not be to everyones liking, detracting slightly from the overall experience. However, a more pressing concern is the presence of stray dogs within the premises. This poses a significant safety risk, especially for children. Instances of attacks on kids by these dogs have been reported, highlighting the urgent need for the establishment to address this issue and ensure the safety of all patrons. Despite these concerns, Tim Hortons remains a popular destination, though improvements in safety measures are crucial for a truly enjoyable experience.

review_text: I went with the expectations of the same Canadian Tim hortons, but got highly disappointed. I wanted to order iced cappuccino with whip cream and bagel with cheese. I tasted ice cubes in ice latte while drinking. And the whip cream they used is the one for cake making not for this purpose(the texture of it should have been a lot less thicker and a drop sugar not a blast of sugar and not extremely thick) however actual Tim hortons and also the Dubai branch makes it with crushed ice. So they don t know the recipe. All in all they DIDNOT have anything in the menu as Tim hortons. It s highly priced. So I highly suggest to not to go there just for the sake of its name. Suggestion to the cafe to change the name from Tim hortons to their own desired name as their own desired menu in Tim hortons.

review_text: We went here expecting a diner, found a cafe instead, but the rates werent remotely related to a cafes menu card. Lots of parking, Google location is off by 50 metres Theres limited seating ( about 12 seats) in the air conditioned section. I went with family.. waited 25 minutes for a table in the AC section. When we got it, twas a small table meant for 2 people, with 3 chairs.. ( Zomato reservation doesnt count ) We could have sat in the open, but there were dogs sleeping below the seats, and the fans werent blowing enough air to keep it cool. (We started perspiring while waiting.) Their QR code based order app/ link doesnt work either. The gateman was very nice, hence,  I gave you an extra star for his service. There was no table service, considering that you charge 300/- for a crossaint, the least you can do is give me service? After placing the order, a pager token was given to us. Wait time is 20 minutes post placing the order. If you are really hungry, please find a better establishment that will give you value for your money Parking: Outside the shop, if you drive a two wheeler when alone or with one other person, theres more than 150 slots here. However if you drive a gas guzzling XL size SUV even though theres only 2 of you, well theres about 12 -15 slots.

review_text: My recent visit to Tim Hortons in Lokhandwala left me utterly disappointed. The hype surrounding their coffee and food is, in my experience, unwarranted. Firstly, the taste of the items I tried was nothing short of sad. The pastries were terrible, lacking the freshness and flavor that one would expect. The coffee, often raved about, was no more than sugar shots that left me longing for the richness and depth of flavor I anticipated. Service, unfortunately, was equally lackluster. The servers mixed up orders, leading to confusion and unnecessary delays. It was clear that the staff was struggling to keep up with the demand, and this affected the overall customer experience. Considering my underwhelming experience at Tim Hortons in Lokhandwala, I cannot recommend this establishment. There are far better options in the area for those seeking a quality coffee and dining experience.

review_text: Tim Hortons - Stepped in for a French Vanilla Black and a chocolate pastry, both of which knocked it out of the park. Seriously, that pastry could write a memoir about how awesome it is, and Id read it. But lets talk wait times oh, the wait times. I had enough time to ponder the existential crises of my life while waiting for that cup of joe. Its as if each coffee bean is being individually interviewed before making it into the grinder. And our baristas? Bless their hearts, they could use a training montage. Think Rocky, but with espresso machines instead of punching bags. Still, despite the time warp and the barista learning curve, the coffee and pastry did not disappoint. They were the saving grace, like finding a Rs 500 bill in an old pair of jeans. Id give it a solid 7 out of 10. Why? Because the flavors were the heroes of this story, swooping in to save the day, while everything else was, lets say, a work in progress. Would I go back? Absolutely, but Ill bring War and Peace to read while I wait.

review_text: Tim Hortons opened up in Mumbai recently and we finally got the opportunity to visit this place. We wanted to have their Frozen Vanilla Frappe which is their best selling but that was sold out by the time we went (around 9 PM) Taking you through everything that we ordered. Java Chip The next best in their list after Vanilla Frappe and it was quite a fulfilling treat. TimBits Surely the best thing we had here. They had four varieties, Blueberry filled, Chocolate filled, Caramel Crumble & Cookies and Cream. All of them were amazing but we personally loved Blueberry and Chocolate fillings. It is also priced at a very reasonable price of 39Rs per piece so dont miss out. Donuts We tried their Chocolate Brownie and Blueberry Cheesecake donut. If you like blueberry, you are definitely going to love this. Dipped in blueberry glaze with some blueberry cheesecake filling, it was the ultimate desserts fest for us at Tim Hortons. We loved the desserts so much here that we actually got a sugar rush. Cant wait to visit again and try more things. Tim Hortons was amazing overall!

review_text: I finally visited Tim Hortons first time after waiting for so long! The first impression was - wow! Located at just the perfect location on Andheri backroad, the cafe has massive space with several tables inside and outside to fit at lease 50 people at once. The menu was vast and it took forever to choose what my bestie and wanted to have. After thinking for long and drooling over delicious-looking food on the rack, we went ahead with BBQ Chicken Piadina and Baida Cigar Rolls. Baida Cigar Roll was simple and nice. Was a bit oily like spring rolls, but it was a good delight. The green chutney that came along was out of the world and super delicious, just like typical Punjabi Ghar ka chutney. BBQ Chicken Piadina was super flavourful and delicious. The chicken was soft and fresh, nicely cooked in flavourful sauce. The Piadina was enough cheesy and creamy. Onions and green chillies added a nice punch. We also tried and loved all four flavours of Timbits. Loved them so much that we took take aways for the family as well. Cafe Mocha was nice, light and refreshing. Overall, I loved every bit of the place, right from the food we had to the vibe! Was to visit here to try rest of the menu super soon!

review_text: Tried Tim for the first time. Liked the vibe and ambience. Have compared my recent experience to that of Starbucks since I have been a fan since it s launch in India. Sharing a detailed review below: Food: A variety of good options. Tried multiple things here. They have adapted the taste as per Indian palate. The prep time is a bit long since I have experienced Starbucks which is much faster. Ambience: The is decent, basic and standard as expected from an international brand. The best part is comfy open air seating. Hygiene: This is a miss big time. Especially the washrooms. I have never experienced unclean toilets in Starbucks with my over 100+ visits in multiple cities. This one was unclean and smelly. Had spent almost 5-6 hours working from here. Didn t notice anyone cleaning it up. Also, nothing specific to the store. But the mobile range is poor if you plan to sit inside. Seems to be some network issue inside the store. Made it difficult to operate from there. The other observation was that though the store wasn t busy as much on a Friday afternoon. But around 50% of the tables were occupied by Tim staff. There was food trails and tasting happening, areas manager was taking some call. New joiners we re taking up calls from customer facing area. Making it hard for me to find a table with charging capacity as most of them were already being used. There is long way to go for Tim to level up and match up to Starbucks in India.
